lead_paragraph: Making an Olympic debut aged 54 is some feat in itself, but for Brazilian trap shooter Janice Teixeira it surely comes second to confounding medics with a remarkable recovery from a stroke.

headline.print_headline: Stroke Survivor Making Games Debut Aged 54
